.TH TMUX-RESTORE-SESSION 1 "2026-06-30" "tmux-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tmux-restore-session \- restore a tmux session saved by tmux-save-session
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tmux-restore-session
.RB [ -d
.IR dir | --dir
.IR dir ]
.RB [ --no-attach ]
.RI [ session-name ]
.br
.B tmux-restore-session
.RB [ -d
.IR dir | --dir
.IR dir ]
.B --list
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tmux-restore-session
runs an executable restore script produced by
.BR tmux-save-session (1).
When no session name is supplied, it restores the only saved session directly
or opens an
.BR fzf (1)
picker when multiple saved sessions exist.
.PP
After restoring, the command attaches from outside tmux and switches the
current client from inside tmux unless
.B --no-attach
is set.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI -d ", --dir " dir
Directory where restore scripts are read.
.TP
.BR -l ", " --list
List saved sessions and exit.
.TP
.B --no-attach
Restore without attaching or switching clients.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show usage.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TMUX_TOOLS_SESSION_DIR
Default session directory. If unset, the default is
.IR ${XDG_DATA_HOME:-$HOME/.local/share}/tmux/sessions .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The session was restored or listed.
.TP
.B 1
No matching saved session exists or restore failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tmux-save-session (1),
.BR fzf (1),
.BR tmux (1)
